<div id="content">
    
<h1>Stores</h1>
    <!-- Image For Store 1 -->
    <div class="row">
    <div class="col s12 m4">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-image">
          <img src="http://cms.ipressroom.com.s3.amazonaws.com/226/files/201710/Baskin-Robbins+Store+Front.jpg">
        </div>
        <div class="card-content">
          <span class="card-title">Baskin Robbins</span>
          <p>Our famous Baskin Robbins store offers a wide variety of flavors 
            to choose from. Best of all, Limited flavors are offered monthly and
            branded as our Flavor of the Month. Be sure to keep updated on 
            what's new in this web app.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- Image For Store 2 -->
    <div class="col s12 m4">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-image">
          <img src="https://www.wattisretail.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Haagen-Dazs-Hackescher-Markt2.jpg">
        </div>
        <div class="card-content">
          <span class="card-title">Haagen Daz</span>
          <p>Refine your moments in this luxurious 5 star store like never before. 
          Enjoy exclusive amenities such as VIP dash lanes and Daz Points. 
          Curated for the lovers of Ice-Creams</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <!-- Image For Store 3 -->
    <div class="col s12 m4">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-image">
          <img src="https://www.ft.com/__origami/service/image/v2/images/raw/https%3A%2F%2Fs3-ap-northeast-1.amazonaws.com%2Fpsh-ex-ftnikkei-3937bb4%2Fimages%2F7%2F9%2F4%2F2%2F8112497-1-eng-GB%2F20140124_coldstone.jpg?source=nar-cms">
        </div>
        <div class="card-content">
          <span class="card-title">Cold Stone</span>
          <p>For the young, for the old, this store has it all. Our energized store offers a variety of flavors that youngsters and oldies enjoy together. 
          What's more, this store offers daily preformance of ice-cream dance as you watch it being served to you, that compliments your stay</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
  </div>
  
<hr>

<div class="col s6">
<h5><u>Table Functions</u></h5>
<br>
<%= link_to 'View All Stores', {controller: 'stores', action: 'index'}, :class=>"btn waves-effect waves-light light-blue"  %>
<%= link_to 'View Active Stores', {controller: 'stores', action: 'index', :active => true}, :class=>"btn waves-effect waves-light pink"  %>
<%= link_to 'View Inactive Stores', {controller: 'stores', action: 'index', :inactive => true}, :class => 'waves-effect waves-light btn amber'  %>
<%= link_to 'Sort By Alphabetical', {controller: 'stores', action: 'index', :alphabetical => true}, :class => 'waves-effect waves-light btn grey'  %>
</div>
<br>
<hr>
<br>
<% unless @stores.empty? %>
<table class="highlight responsive-table">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Store ID</th>
      <th>Name</th>
      <th>Street</th>
      <th>City</th>
      <th>State</th>
      <th>Zip</th>
      <th>Phone</th>
      <th>Latitude</th>
      <th>Longitude</th>
      <th>Active</th>
      <th colspan="2"></th>
    </tr>
  </thead>

  <tbody>
    <% @stores.each do |store| %>
      <tr>
        <td><%= link_to store.id, store %></td>
        <td><%= store.name %></td>
        <td><%= store.street %></td>
        <td><%= store.city %></td>
        <td><%= store.state %></td>
        <td><%= store.zip %></td>
        <td><%= store.phone %></td>
        <td><%= store.latitude %></td>
        <td><%= store.longitude %></td>
        <td><%= store.active %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_store_path(store), :class=>"btn waves-effect waves-light light-blue" %></td>
        <td><%= link_to 'Destroy', store, method: :delete, data: { confirm: 'Are you sure?' }, :class => 'waves-effect waves-light btn pink' %></td>
      </tr>
    <% end %>
  </tbody>
</table>

<br>

<% else %>
<h5><strong><font color="red">No Records Found!</font></strong></h5>
<% end %>


<!-- Add the pagination using will_paginate gem -->
<span class="paginate">
<%= will_paginate @stores, :previous_label => "Previous&nbsp;", :next_label => "&nbsp;Next" %>
</span>

<br>

</div>
